<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Challenge">Challenge<a class="anchor-link" href="#Challenge">¶</a></h2><p>Depending on classification, many no of actions are possible.</p>
$$
2^n \text{percepts} \rightarrow 2^m \text{actions}
$$<p>Why $2^n$? Given a set of percepts, there would be $2^n$ combinations possible. Each percept is either selected or not, so this results in a binomial theorem situation.</p>
<p>Suppose we have $n=3$ percepts, then there are $2^3$ combinations possible. Each combination's <em>digit</em> is indication if a percept is selected or not.</p>
<p>Let X indicate random variable if a percept is selected(head) or not(tails), so $X = H,T$. Let $n$ indicate no of percepts (at each selection layer, we select one percept or not select). Then the tree could be as below. The digit position could indicate the percept number.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">
<div class="input">
<div class="prompt input_prompt">In [3]:</div>
<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">graphviz</span> <span class="k">import</span> <span class="n">Digraph</span>
<span class="kn">from</span> <span class="nn">coinflipviz</span> <span class="k">import</span> <span class="n">draw_graph</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">get_combinations</span>

<span class="n">n_flips</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">3</span>  <span class="c1"># we have 3 percepts</span>

<span class="n">g</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Digraph</span><span class="p">()</span>
<span class="n">g</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">draw_graph</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">g</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">n_flips</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">g</span>
</pre></div>

</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>So 8 combinations in each of which, a percept might be selected or not. For eg, $THH$ indicates 1st percept not selected and rest two selected.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Equivalence-Classes">Equivalence Classes<a class="anchor-link" href="#Equivalence-Classes">¶</a></h2><p>Simply convert $2^n$ percepts to $k$ concepts.</p>
<p><img alt="2019-06-17_15h41_28.png" src="data:image/png;base64, "/></p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Concept-Hierarchies">Concept Hierarchies<a class="anchor-link" href="#Concept-Hierarchies">¶</a></h2><p>Often top down..</p>
<h3 id="Establish-&amp;-Refine">Establish &amp; Refine<a class="anchor-link" href="#Establish-&amp;-Refine">¶</a></h3><p><img alt="2019-06-17_15h45_24.png" src="data:image/png;base64, "/></p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>Imagine in above hierarchy, once we establish Eagle and Bluebird as birds, then a characterisitic like Size could help us differentiate between Eagle and Bluebird, so size could be a new node downwards. In below example, if all are yes in Eager, Bluebird, Penguin, then base class Bird has that charactersitic as Yes.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p><img alt="2019-06-17_15h48_43.png" src="data:image/png;base64, "/></p>
<blockquote><p>May not work all situations</p>
</blockquote>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Types-of-Concepts">Types of Concepts<a class="anchor-link" href="#Types-of-Concepts">¶</a></h2><p><img alt="2019-06-17_15h55_49.png" src="data:image/png;base64, "/></p>
<h3 id="Axiomatic-Concepts">Axiomatic Concepts<a class="anchor-link" href="#Axiomatic-Concepts">¶</a></h3><p>Formal set of necessary and sufficient conditions. Easy to program. Easy to communicate.</p>
<p>Eg: Circle; all points in a plane that are equidistant from a single point.</p>
<h3 id="Prototype-Concepts">Prototype Concepts<a class="anchor-link" href="#Prototype-Concepts">¶</a></h3><blockquote><p>Base concepts defined by typical example with overridable propoerties</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Eg: Chair. Note base class has default values, and children overrides some of the notions..</p>
<p><img alt="2019-06-17_15h58_11.png" src="data:image/png;base64, "/></p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="Exemplar-Concepts">Exemplar Concepts<a class="anchor-link" href="#Exemplar-Concepts">¶</a></h3><p>Defined by implicit abstractions of instances or exemplars of concept.</p>
<p>Eg: Beauty</p>
<p><img alt="2019-06-17_15h59_44.png" src="data:image/png;base64, "/></p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h3 id="Qulia">Qulia<a class="anchor-link" href="#Qulia">¶</a></h3><p>Much lesser formal than Exemplar - raw sensation from senses (eg, bitterness)</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">
</div><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Bottom-Up-Search">Bottom-Up Search<a class="anchor-link" href="#Bottom-Up-Search">¶</a></h2><p>From values of leaf nodes, predict about the root node..</p>
<p><img alt="2019-06-17_16h08_52.png" src="data:image/png;base64, "/></p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
